HEADWORD: Obole
<hw>Ob"ole</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>obole</ets>. See <er>Obolus</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Old Pharm.)</fld>
<def>A weight of twelve grains; or, according to some, of ten grains, or
half a scruple.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>obol</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obolize</ent>⟦br⟧
